Description: Handle sliver of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine light orange-brown. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Pencil '320' and circled '208'. Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 200, 15 Name Aischinas. A stamp from the same die comes from Crocodilopolis (001 KF 041/100041).
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1166)
